{
  "texts": [
    "The circuit is used to program a variety of high-dimensional quantum gates and serves as a generalized multioutcome device.",
    "The circular inset shows a coincidence image depicting a five-outcome measurement in basis μ = 1 performed with the Fourier gate 𝔽𝔽 at Bob.",
    "The image is obtained by scanning a detector across the output of the circuit, conditioned on the measurement of Πμ=1 a=0 at Alice, and shows a large intensity in mode 0 due to strong spatial-mode correlations.",
    "Coincidence detection events between Alice and Bob are registered by time-tagging electronics.",
    "b, Charge-coupled device images demonstrating the operation of the Fourier gate 𝔽𝔽 as a multioutcome measurement of classical macro-pixel modes prepared in basis μ = 1 in dimensions d = {2, 3, 5}."
  ]
}